## Lab 4 — Active Established Connections

### Command

```bash
sudo netstat -an | grep ESTABLISHED | awk '{print $5}' | cut -d: -f2 | sort -u
```

This extracts the **remote port numbers** from all currently established TCP connections.

### Output

```
443
4860
67
```

### Analysis

| Port | Protocol | What it means |
|------|----------|---------------|
| **443** | HTTPS | Active encrypted web connection (browser, updates, etc.) |
| **4860** | Google QUIC/alt-HTTPS | Connection to a Google service |
| **67** | DHCP | DHCP lease maintenance with router |

> **Note:** Port 67 showing in established connections is unusual for DHCP (which is typically UDP). This may reflect the DHCP client state being tracked differently by netstat on this kernel/distro.

