## Commands Reference

```bash
# Capture TCP SYN/ACK packets
sudo tcpdump -i any -n 'tcp[tcpflags] & (tcp-syn|tcp-ack) != 0' -c 6 -w tcp-handshake.pcap

# Read pcap file
tcpdump -r tcp-handshake.pcap -n

# Capture DNS (UDP port 53)
sudo tcpdump -i any udp port 53 -c 5 -w udp-traffic.pcap

# Show listening services
sudo netstat -tulpn | grep LISTEN

# Show remote ports of established connections
sudo netstat -an | grep ESTABLISHED | awk '{print $5}' | cut -d: -f2 | sort -u
```

